      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: trust all ClawHub channel types when package matches official catalog",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes issue #92516: ClawHub official-channel installs for npm-only catalog entries (like Microsoft Teams) were not trusted.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n## Real behavior proof\n\n\n**Behavior addressed**: ClawHub official-channel installs should be trusted when the package matches the official catalog, regardless of whether the entry has clawhubSpec or npmSpec.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Local OpenClaw setup with Node.js 24\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```bash\n$ node --import tsx scripts/repro/issue-92516-clawhub-trust.mts\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n```\n=== Reproduction for issue #92516 ===\nTesting ClawHub official-channel install for npm-only catalog entry (msteams)...\n✓ npm-only ClawHub official install trusted\n\nTesting that ClawHub community channel is NOT trusted...\n✓ Community channel correctly NOT trusted\n\nTesting that ClawHub private channel is NOT trusted...\n✓ Private channel correctly NOT trusted\n\nPASS: ClawHub official-channel installs are trusted for npm-only catalog entries.\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**: npm-only ClawHub official-channel installs (like Microsoft Teams) are now trusted, while community/private channels correctly remain untrusted.\n\n**What was not tested**: Production self-hosted deployments with actual Microsoft Teams channel.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **src/plugins/manifest-registry.ts**: Trust ClawHub official-channel installs for npm-only catalog entries\n- **src/plugins/manifest-registry.test.ts**: Added test coverage\n- **scripts/repro/issue-92516-clawhub-trust.mts**: Updated reproduction script\n\nFixes #92516",
        "branch": "fix/92516-clawhub-channel-trust",
